    (shape input) (at 160 170 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify right)))
  (hierarchical_label "LCD_BL_PWM"
    (shape output) (at 160 174 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify right)))

  ;; I2C to connectivity sheet (Qwiic/Grove share same bus)
  (hierarchical_label "I2C_SDA"
    (shape bidirectional) (at 40 150 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify right)))
  (hierarchical_label "I2C_SCL"
    (shape output) (at 40 154 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify right)))

  ;;
  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ;;
  (text "ESP32-S3-WROOM-1-N16R8 — CO-PROCESSOR NOTES:\n\nWIRELESS: The S3 radio (WiFi/BLE) is NOT USED in this design.\nAll wireless is handled by the ESP32-C6 on the Super Carrier.\nThe PCB antenna on the WROOM-1 is non-functional by design.\nDo NOT attempt to enable S3 WiFi in firmware — it will conflict with C6 RF.\n\nPSRAM: GPIO35, GPIO36, GPIO37 are internally connected to the octal PSRAM.\nThey appear as castellated pads but cannot be used as general-purpose GPIO.\nTreat as NC on the PCB. Do not route signals to these pads.\n\nGPIO0 (CS_S3_MPU on carrier):\nGPIO0 is a strapping pin — must be HIGH at boot for normal operation.\nCS_S3_MPU is active-LOW. The 10kΩ pullup R11 holds it HIGH at boot.\nSatisfies strapping requirement. This is a safe and well-established pattern.\nOn the shield, GPIO0 is NC (CS_S3_MPU not needed — MPU not on shield).\n\nUART0 vs USB CDC:\nGPIO43/44 are the default UART0 pins. These are reassigned to the SPI2\ndisplay bus (GPIO43=LCD_RST, GPIO44=TOUCH_INT) in this design.\nAll S3 debug output uses USB CDC on GPIO19/20 (J5 USB-C connector).\nUSB CDC provides printf(), logging, and JTAG debugging — no UART needed.\n\nSPI2 vs SPI3:\nSPI2 (LCD_CAM peripheral): GPIO17=CLK, GPIO18=MOSI, GPIO11=CS, GPIO16=DC\n  → 5\" TFT display. 80MHz. Write-only (no MISO needed for display).\nSPI3 (GPSPI controller): GPIO14=SCK, GPIO13=MOSI, GPIO12=MISO, GPIO10=CS\n  → UNO Q interface. Slave mode. STM32U585 is master.\n\nI2C bus (GPIO8/9) shared between:\n  ES8388 codec control (address 0x10 or 0x11 per ADDR pin)\n  GT911 capacitive touch controller (address 0x5D or 0x14)\n  Both are I2C slaves at different addresses — no conflict.\n  1kΩ pullups R3/R4 sized for ES8388. 4.7kΩ for GT911 on display FPC.\n  Net effective pullup with both in parallel: ~820Ω. Acceptable at 400kHz."
    (at 30 185 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
)
